
                           Privacy Statement for 1st Team Veterans Service Organization





Effective Date: October 18, 2024




Introduction

At 1st Team Veterans Service Organization ("1st Team"), we are committed to safeguarding the privacy and security of our clients' information. This Privacy Statement outlines our practices regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of personal data, particularly for our clientsâ€™ protected business data and any data governed by HIPAA, NIST, FISMA, and other related governmental regulations.

Information We Collect

1. Personal Information: We may collect personal information such as names, email addresses, phone numbers, and other identifiers relevant to our services.
2. Health Information: In connection with our services, we may collect health-related data that is subject to HIPAA protections.
3. Business Data: We handle sensitive business data for our clients, ensuring compliance with relevant regulations.

Use of Information

1st Team uses the information we collect for various purposes, including:
- Providing and managing our services.
- Communicating with clients regarding their services and inquiries.
- Complying with applicable laws and regulations.
- Conducting research and analysis to improve our services.

 Data Protection

We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect the personal information of our clients against unauthorized access, loss, or damage. This includes:
- Secure storage solutions that comply with NIST and FISMA standards.
- Regular audits and assessments to ensure compliance with HIPAA regulations.

 Disclosure of Information

1st Team does not sell or rent personal data to third parties. We may disclose personal information in the following circumstances:
- To comply with legal obligations or respond to lawful requests from governmental authorities.
- To protect and defend our rights and property.
- To prevent harm or financial loss in connection with our services.

 Regulatory Contacts

For any inquiries or concerns regarding compliance, please contact the appropriate regulatory authority:

1. Department of Veterans Affairs (VA)
   - Contact: [Your VA Regional Office Contact](https://www.va.gov/contact-us/) 
   - Phone: 1-800-827-1000
   - Website: [Department of Veterans Affairs](https://www.va.gov)

2. Office for Civil Rights (OCR) - HHS
   - Contact: Director of the Office for Civil Rights
   - Phone: 1-800-368-1019 (TDD: 1-800-537-7697)
   - Email: ocrmail@hhs.gov
   - Website: [HHS OCR](https://www.hhs.gov/ocr/index.html)

3. National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST)
   - Contact: Cybersecurity Framework Team
   - Phone: 301-975-2000
   - Email: cybersecurityframework@nist.gov
   - Website: [NIST Cybersecurity Framework](https://www.nist.gov/cyberframework)

4. Federal Risk and Authorization Management Program (FedRAMP)
   - Contact: FedRAMP PMO
   - Phone: 1-877-696-2240
   - Email: info@fedramp.gov
   - Website: [FedRAMP](https://www.fedramp.gov)

5. Defense Information Systems Agency (DISA)
   - Contact: DISA Help Desk
   - Phone: 1-844-347-2457 (DSN: 850-1900)
   - Email: disa.meade.its.mbx.help-desk@mail.mil
   - Website: [DISA](https://www.disa.mil)

 Changes to This Privacy Statement

We may update our Privacy Statement from time to time. We will notify clients of any changes by posting the new Privacy Statement on our website with the updated effective date.

